Package: phosh-pam-duress
Version: 1
Architecture: arm64
Maintainer: Sirr_Org
Depends: libpam0g, libssl3
Recommends: libpam-runtime
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/Sirr-os/phosh-pam-duress
Description: PAM duress module - authenticate under coercion
 pam_duress is a PAM module that allows a system administrator to
 define a duress password. When a user authenticates with the duress
 password instead of their real password, the PAM session succeeds
 (to avoid alerting an attacker), while silently executing a
 configurable script in the background.
. 
 This package includes:
  - pam_duress.so   — PAM shared module (/lib/security/)
  - duress_sign     — utility to sign duress scripts
  - pam_test        — testing utility for PAM stacks
